<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP19.HTM#AS547234">Encryption products: </A><DD>Escrowed encryption to dampen market for unescrowed encryption products to provide similar security without features for government exceptional access 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AS40510">Encryption systems: </A><DD>Efforts increased to develop encryption systems for private sector use and integrate encryption with other information technology products 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP4.HTM#AS13882">Encryption technology: </A><DD>Controls used to deny potential adversaries access to U. S. encryption technology to reveal important characteristics of U. S. information security products or used to thwart U. S. attempts at collecting signals intelligence information 1 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP9.HTM#AS27920">Escrow: </A><DD>U. S. government to specify responsibilities, obligations and liabilities of escrow agents 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP19.HTM#AS54765">Escrow-encrypted data: </A><DD>Sensitive information to remain secure but enables law enforcement and national security authorities to obtain access to escrow-encrypted data in specific instances when authorized by law 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AS229128">Escrowed Encryption Standard: </A><DD>U. S. government's promotion initiatives include Escrowed Encryption Standard for secure voice telephony 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AS198172">Escrowed keys: </A><DD>Hastens deployment of escrowed encryption in other countries because shipment of escrowed encryption products need not to be delayed until completion of formal agreements regarding transfer of escrowed keys across international boundaries 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP2.HTM#AS65249">Espionage: </A><DD>Cryptography to protect trade secrets and proprietary information of businesses and reduce economic espionage 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AS3324">Espionage: </A><DD>Committee believes that recommendations to lead to enhanced confidentiality and protection of information for individuals and companies reducing economic and financial crimes and economic espionage from domestic and foreign sources 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP27.HTM#AS721140">Europe: </A><DD>Crook held positions in top management for Motorola Corporation in United States and Europe 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP26.HTM#AS713110">European Command: </A><DD>Military posts include deputy commander in chief of European Command in Germany 
<P>
</DL>


