<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP3.HTM#AS9567">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Broad picture of cryptography policy to be understood on unclassified basis, no findings or recommendations held back on basis of classification and report being unclassified in entirety 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP3.HTM#AS1035">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Framework for national cryptography policy to provide coherent structure and reduce uncertainty for potential vendors and nongovernment and government users of cryptography in ways 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP3.HTM#AS11311">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy to be developed by executive and legislative branches on basis of open public discussion and governed by rule of law 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP3.HTM#AS1154">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Cryptography policy being issue in which segments of population being stakeholders and invocation of official government secrecy in area having led to public distrust and resistance 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP3.HTM#AS115346">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Congressional involvement in debate over cryptography policy being asset rather than liability 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP4.HTM#AS11912">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy affecting development and use of commercial cryptography to be more aligned with market forces 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP4.HTM#AS12127">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy having become disconnected from market reality and needs of parties in private sector 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP4.HTM#AS1257">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy aligned with market forces to emphasize freedom of domestic users to determine cryptographic functionality, protection and implementations according to security needs as see fit 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP4.HTM#AS1273">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Standards being another dimension of national cryptography policy with significant impact on commercial cryptography and market 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP4.HTM#AS127105">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy being more aligned with market forces to encourage adoption by federal government and private parties of cryptographic standards being consistent with prevailing industry practice 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP4.HTM#AS12950">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy to support use of algorithms, product designs and product implementations being open to public scrutiny 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AS2298">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Approach of U. S. government to problems to arise from use of encryption being aggressive promotion of escrowed encryption as pillar of technical foundation for national cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AS247127">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy not supported nonconfidentiality uses 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AS26710">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>U. S. government aggressively promoted escrowed encryption as pillar of technical foundation for national cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP9.HTM#AS285103">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Process begun at Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development in December 1995 being promising forum in which nations to bring representatives from business, law enforcement and national security to discuss matters related to cryptography policy over national borders 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AS3126">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Committee asked to address national cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AS31275">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Changes in national cryptography policy to have little operational impact on U. S. information security 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AS320217">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Committee believes that policy-making process requires better ways for representing broadly government and nongovernment interests in cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AS322207">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Broad outlines of national cryptography policy to be argued on unclassified basis 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AS34013">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy to be developed by executive and legislative branches on basis of open public discussion and governed by rule of law 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AS34213">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy affecting development and use of commercial cryptography to be more aligned with market forces 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AS40197">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Cryptography policy reflected U. S. government's needs for effective cryptographic protection of classified and other sensitive communications 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS41819">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Technology trends with national cryptography policy to keep pace 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS42244">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>U. S. government that describes national cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS42425">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Interests affected by national cryptography policy being multiple, varied and related 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS42623">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Debate over cryptography policy hampered by incomplete analysis and discussion of policy options 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS43014">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>National cryptography policy involves large number of important issues 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS43042">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Important to national cryptography policy as well issues related to deployment of large-scale infrastructure for cryptography and legislation and regulations to support use of cryptography for authentication and data integrity purposes 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS434130">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Study built upon three prior efforts to examine national cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS4404">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Subject of national cryptography policy being complex 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS4426">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Report being not comprehensive study of grand trade-offs to be made in other dimensions of national policy to compensate for changes in cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AS442226">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Report provide information to help to assess impact of approaches to cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AS448211">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Current study draws on report and others to extent relevant for analysis, findings and conclusions about cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AS4506">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Report being not study of patent disputes having arisen with respect to national cryptography policy in past several years 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP16.HTM#AS486166">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Committee not even find clear written statement of national cryptography policy that went beyond general statements 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP16.HTM#AS488152">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Administration officials wished that discourse on national cryptography policy to have unfolded differently 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP16.HTM#AS502113">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Dorothy Denning of Georgetown University provided useful papers concerning law enforcement perspective on cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP17.HTM#AS504437">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Prior work on previous NRC report on standards provided important point of departure for committee's discussion on standards as apply to cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP17.HTM#AS504516">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Prior experience in computer and information security being invaluable in framing discussion of technical issues in cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP25.HTM#AS67050">Cryptography policy: </A><DD>Secretary of Defense to request National Research Council of National Academy of Sciences to conduct comprehensive study of cryptographic technologies and national cryptography policy 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP16.HTM#AS492347">Cryptography policy meeting of Organization: </A><DD>Participate in first-ever cryptography policy meeting of Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development and Business Industry Advisory Council, provided occasion for extended give-and-take discussions with government officials and private stakeholders 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP17.HTM#AS528291">Cryptography policy source: </A><DD>Cryptography policy source books published annually by Electronic Privacy Information Center in Washington 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP16.HTM#AS4785">Cryptography's Role: </A><DD>Title of report being Cryptography's Role in Securing Information Society 
<P>
</DL>


