[7] For example, following press reports of deciphered Libyan messages before and after a bombing in West Berlin in which an 
American soldier died, Libya changed its communications codes.  A senior<A NAME = "AO53166"></A><A NAME = "AS53167"></A><A NAME = "AS53168"></A><A NAME = "AS53169"></A> American official was quoted as saying that the subsequent 
Libyan<A NAME = "AB53191"></A> purchase of advanced cryptographic equipment from a Swiss firm was &quot;one of the prices [the United<A NAME = "BB531126"></A><A HREF = "SPP27.HTM#BB721170"><img src="CIRCLINK.GIF"></A> States is] paying for 
having revealed, in order to marshal support of our allies and public opinion, that intercepted communications<A NAME = "AB531169"></A> traffic provided 
evidence that Libya was behind the bombing of the Berlin disco.&quot;  See &quot;Libyans Buy Message-Coding Equipment,&quot; <I>Washington 
Post</I>, April 22, 1986, p. A-8.<BR>

