<P>
<A NAME = "AE1500"></A><A NAME = "AE1500"></A><A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO16066"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Fact suggests export of cryptography to be regulated under Commerce Control List <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO160120"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptography being critical military application For which few technical alternatives being available <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO160158"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>USML designed to regulate technologies with applications for reasons of national security <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO160190"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Retention of controls to mitigate loss to U. S. national security interests in short term <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO160227"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Allow United States to evaluate impact of relaxation on national security interests before making changes and buy time for U. S. national security authorities to adjust to new technical reality <P>
<A NAME = "AK164"></A><H3><B>Specific Recommendations</B></H3><P><A NAME = "AE1560"></A><A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO1681"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendations 4.1 and 4.2 below describe committee's judgments about expeditious changes to present export control regime to result in better alignment with technological and market trends <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO16867"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation 4.3 intended to promote other important changes in export control regime to reduce uncertainty about export control licensing process and eliminate unnecessary friction between export control regime and affected <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO1701"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendations 4.1 and 4.2 describe changes to current export control regime <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO17051"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Two features of current export regime being desirable to warrant special attention <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO170124"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Products being products that provide confidentiality only for use in banking or money transactions and products limited in functionality to providing capabilities for authentication, access control and data integrity without capabilities for confidentiality <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO170209"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Second feature of current export regime to be continued being United States to maintain embargo on exports of products with encryption capabilities to rogue nations <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO1723"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Relaxation of U. S. export controls being only first step on road to greater use of cryptography around world <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO17253"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Foreign nations decide that national interests threatened by cryptography <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO172111"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. vendors to be faced with need to develop products with encryption capabilities on nation-by-nation basis <P>
<A NAME = "AE1650"></A><A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO1743"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation 4.1, Products providing confidentiality at level that meets general commercial requirements to be exportable 2 <P>
<A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO17453"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Products with encryption capabilities that incorporate 56-bit DES algorithm provide level of confidentiality and exportable <P>
<A NAME = "AE1670"></A><A HREF = "SPP5.HTM#AO1783"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Products covered under Recommendation 4.1 to be designed in way to preclude repeated use to increase confidentiality beyond acceptable level <P>
<A NAME = "AE1680"></A><A NAME = "AE1680"></A><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1803"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Vendors of products covered under Recommendation 4.1 to provide to U. S. government full technical specifications of product and reasonable technical assistance upon request in order to assist U. S. government in understanding product's internal operations <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO180106"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Product complies with conditions required for export jurisdiction under CCL <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO180132"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Appropriate nondisclosure agreements to protect vendors' interests in proprietary information embedded in products <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO180168"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Requirement to allow more cost-effective use of intelligence budgets for understanding design of exported cryptographic systems <P>
<A NAME = "AE1720"></A><A NAME = "AE1720"></A><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1825"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Level of cryptographic strength that determines threshold of easy exportability to be set at level that promotes broad use of cryptography and adjusted upward periodically as technology evolves <P>
<A NAME = "AE1730"></A><A NAME = "AE1730"></A><A NAME = "AE1730"></A><A NAME = "AE1730"></A><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1843"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Public-key protection of secret keys used by products covered by Recommendation 4.1 to be allowed at least as strong as cryptographic protection of message or file text provided by products with appropriate safety margins that protect against possible attacks on public-key algorithms <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO18611"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Products that incorporate 56-bit DES for confidentiality meet <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO18653"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Ability to use 56-bit DES abroad to enhance confidentiality available to U. S. multinational corporations conducting business overseas with foreign partners, suppliers and customers and improve choice of products with encryption capabilities available to domestic users <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO186138"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation 4.1 to help United States to maintain worldwide market leadership in products with encryption capabilities <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO186186"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee believes that foreign customers unwilling to overlook perceived weaknesses of 40-bit RC2/RC4 encryption likely to accept DES-based encryption as adequate <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO186269"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Global market acceptance of U. S. products incorporating DES-based encryption being more conducive to U. S. national security interests in intelligence collection than market acceptance of foreign products incorporating even stronger algorithm and key size combinations to emerge to fill vacuum if U. S. export controls <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1883"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee believes that DES being appropriate because gained acceptance as standard for secret-key cryptography within United States and world <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO188207"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Bottom line for committee being DES being good enough for information security applications and likely to be good enough for next decade <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO188275"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Highly motivated and well-funded organizations to be capable of sustaining brute-force attacks on DES during time <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1903"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee recognizes that replacement for DES to be needed in not-so-distant future <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO19040"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Product designers and users to be well advised to anticipate need for future products using DES replacement to be compatible with products <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO190115"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Record of public scrutiny and practical experience being necessary to engender public confidence and waiting for replacement to achieve <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO190210"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Relieve pressures on export control regime stemming from commercial users needing to improve security and give United States and other nations time to formulate long-term global solution <P>
<A NAME = "AE1860"></A><A NAME = "AE1860"></A><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1923"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee recognizes that adoption of Recommendation 4.1 to have negative impact on collection of signals intelligence <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO19255"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>General intelligence produced depends on ability to monitor and select items of interest from large volumes of communications sent in clear <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO192217"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Foreign users of selected channels of high-interest communications not to be expected to purchase and use U. S. encryption products under circumstances and cases not to be affected by change in U. S. export control regime <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO192366"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation 5 addresses measures to help national security authorities to develop capabilities necessary to deal with negative impact <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO192414"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation 4.1 on collection of signals intelligence <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1943"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation 4.2, Products providing stronger confidentiality to be exportable on expedited basis to list of approved companies if proposed product user willing to provide access to decrypted information upon legally authorized request <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1961"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation 4.1 addresses needs of general commercial users <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO19622"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recognizing need for encryption stronger than available under CCL <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO19654"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Administration proposed to give liberal export consideration to software products with 64-bit encryption provided that products escrowed with qualified escrow agent <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO196122"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Proposal being wide foreign availability of strong encryption not damage U. S. intelligence gathering and law enforcement efforts if United States to be assured of access to plaintext when necessary <P>
<A NAME = "AE1960"></A><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO1985"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>From standpoint of U. S. law enforcement interests, continued inclusion on list of approved firms being incentive for company to abide by agreement to provide access to plaintext under proper circumstances <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO19881"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation 4.2 helps to promote escrowed encryption in foreign nations by facilitating deployment in nations of base of products on which governments of relevant nations to build policy regimes supporting escrowed encryption <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO198170"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Hastens deployment of escrowed encryption in other countries because shipment of escrowed encryption products need not to be delayed until completion of formal agreements regarding transfer of escrowed keys across international boundaries <P>
<A NAME = "AE1990"></A><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO2001"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. vendors benefit from Recommendation 4.2 because foreign customers on list of approved companies need not wait for negotiation of formal agreements <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO200102"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptographic keys to be compromised to be reassured that keys to products covered by Recommendation 4.2 to remain within full control <P>
<A NAME = "AE2010"></A><A NAME = "AE2010"></A><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO20238"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. controlled firm to be granted USML license to acquire and export for own use products with encryption capabilities stronger than provided by 40-bit RC2/ RC4 encryption <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO202179"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. controlled/ owned or foreign-owned <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO202202"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Granted USML licenses for stronger cryptography for use in internal communications and communications with other banks even if communications not limited to banking or money transactions <P>
<A NAME = "AE2040"></A><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO20411"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee believes that category to be expanded that U. S. controlled firm being able to acquire and export products covered under Recommendation 4.2 to foreign suppliers and customers for purpose of regular communications with U. S. controlled firm <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO204106"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Number of USML licenses for cryptography implemented just <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO204140"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Purpose of Recommendation 4.2 to make arrangements more systematic and routine <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO2065"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Foreign firms determined by U. S. authorities to be major and trustworthy firms to qualify for list of approved companies <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO20686"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>List of firms eligible for purchasing U. S. products with encryption capabilities or criteria for inclusion on list to be made available upon request <P>
<A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AO20831"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Refusal or inability to cooperate when required well result in company to be dropped from list and publicly identified as noncooperating company and subject parties involved to full range of sanctions being available to enforce compliance of product recipients with end-use restrictions <P>
<A NAME = "AE2100"></A><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO2103"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Firms on list of approved companies being likely to have needs for information security products of highest strength possible for environment <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO21079"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Targets of major concerted cryptanalytic effort described in connection with Recommendation 4.1 <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO210115"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Firms on list of approved companies to agree to provide end-user certification <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO210151"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Exported products to be used only for intrafirm business or foreign parties in regular communications with U. S. firms involved and provide U. S. government with plaintext of encrypted information when presented with authorized law enforcement request and prove that provided plaintext correspond to encrypted information of interest <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO210316"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Compliance with requirements intended to be reasonable precaution that protects against possible risks of diversion to unintended purposes <P>
<A NAME = "AE2150"></A><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO21210"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to streamline and increase transparency of export licensing process for cryptography <P>
<A NAME = "AE2160"></A><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO2143"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee found deal of uncertainty regarding rules, time lines and criteria used in making decisions about exportability of particular products <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO214116"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Presumptive decision for cryptography submitted to State Department for export licensing for approval rather than disapproval <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO214160"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Efforts undertaken in years to streamline State Department's licensing process for cryptography exports to continue and strengthened <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO214219"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to take steps to increase vendor and user understanding of export control regime with intent of bridging gap in perceptions of national security authorities and private sector <P>
<A NAME = "AK218"></A><H3><B>ADJUSTING TO NEW TECHNICAL REALITIES</B></H2><P><A NAME = "AK221"></A><H3><B>Perspective</B></H3><P><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO22340"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptography provides tools to help prevent crime <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO223175"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptography's use by criminals to damage law enforcement mission of investigating and prosecuting individuals who committed crimes <P>
<A NAME = "AE2240"></A><A NAME = "AE2240"></A><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO22523"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Public debate to date focused on impact of cryptography on criminal prosecutions and investigations <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO22567"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee accepts that onset of information age likely to create new challenges for public safety <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO225136"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Law enforcement authorities being unable to gain access to encrypted communications and stored information of criminals <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO225200"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Specific steps to be taken to mitigate difficulties as outlined in Recommendations 5.3 <P>
<A NAME = "AE2280"></A><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO22713"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptography to help to defend vital information assets of United States <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO22755"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptography to impede collection of signals intelligence <P>
<A NAME = "AE2300"></A><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO2297"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Approach of U. S. government to problems to arise from use of encryption being aggressive promotion of escrowed encryption as pillar of technical foundation for national cryptography policy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO229126"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government's promotion initiatives include Escrowed Encryption Standard for secure voice telephony <P>
<A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO229181"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Capstone/Fortezza initiative that provides escrowed encryption capabilities for secure data storage and communications and proposal to liberalize export controls on certain encryption products if keys escrowed <P>
<A NAME = "AE2330"></A><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO2313"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee understands Administration's rationale for promoting escrowed encryption but believes that escrowed encryption to be only one part of strategy for dealing with problems <P>
<A NAME = "AK235"></A><H3><B>Specific Recommendations</B></H3><P><A NAME = "AE2350"></A><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AO23711"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to take steps to assist law enforcement and national security to adjust to new technical realities of information age <P>
<A NAME = "AE2360"></A><A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO23913"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Law enforcement and national security authorities to cope with variety of changing technological circumstances <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO23985"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Explosion of advanced information technologies creating new challenges to law enforcement and national security <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO239133"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Not suffice to bring agencies responsible for law enforcement and national security into information age <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO239181"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Law enforcement and national security demonstrated adaptability to new environments <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO24110"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government actively encourage use of cryptography in nonconfidentiality applications <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO2433"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Nonconfidentiality applications of cryptography not directly threaten law enforcement or national security interests and not in general pose same policy dilemma as confidentiality <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO243101"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Deployment of infrastructures for nonconfidentiality uses of cryptography being necessary condition for use of cryptography for confidentiality <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO243221"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Policy to promote nonconfidentiality applications of cryptography in relevant areas <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO2451"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>One of important of areas concerns protection against systemic national vulnerabilities <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO24565"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Nonconfidentiality uses of cryptography being even more important than capabilities for confidentiality <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO24599"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Ensuring integrity of data that circulates in air traffic control system being almost more important than ensuring confidentiality <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO245147"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Ensuring integrity of data in banking system being more important than ensuring confidentiality <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO247126"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>National cryptography policy not supported nonconfidentiality uses <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO247193"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Government expressed more concern in public debate regarding deleterious impact of use of cryptography for confidentiality <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO2493"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Final dimension of issue being keys used in nonconfidentiality applications of cryptography <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO249107"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Outside access to keys to undermine legal basis and threaten integrity of practices carried out in electronic domain <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO249158"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Whatever benefits to accrue to government authorities acting in interests of public safety or national security from able to forge digital signatures or alter digital data clandestinely to pale by comparison to loss of trust in mechanisms to result from even hint <P>
<A NAME = "AE2530"></A><A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO25110"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to promote security of telecommunications networks more actively <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO25146"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to promote link encryption of cellular communications3 and improvement of security at telephone switches <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO2533"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Public switched telecommunications network being critical to sectors of national economy and undergoing rapid evolution <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO25353"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government having taken steps to improve security of PSTN <P>
<A NAME = "AE2570"></A><A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO2553"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Encryption of wireless voice communications to prevent eavesdropping being easy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP8.HTM#AO25549"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Wireless communications shift from analog to digital modes of transport <P>
