<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP3.HTM#AS9371">Government role: </A><DD>Objective 3 argues that kind of government role in deployment and use of cryptography to continue to be necessary for public safety and national security reasons 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP16.HTM#AS49064">Government service: </A><DD>Committee included individuals with extensive government service and individuals with skepticism about and suspicion of government 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP20.HTM#AS5776">Government standards: </A><DD>Government standards not harm law enforcement or national security 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP9.HTM#AS275144">Government's compulsory process authority: </A><DD>Law enforcement need for access to encrypted records to be substantially met by exercise of government's compulsory process authority for information relevant to investigation and prosecution of criminal activity against encrypted records and relevant cryptographic keys 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AS40196">Government's needs: </A><DD>Cryptography policy reflected U. S. government's needs for effective cryptographic protection of classified and other sensitive communications 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP7.HTM#AS229129">Government's promotion initiatives: </A><DD>U. S. government's promotion initiatives include Escrowed Encryption Standard for secure voice telephony 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP6.HTM#AS19883">Governments of relevant nations: </A><DD>Recommendation 4.2 helps to promote escrowed encryption in foreign nations by facilitating deployment in nations of base of products on which governments of relevant nations to build policy regimes supporting escrowed encryption 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP26.HTM#AS719209">Governors Task Force: </A><DD>Trustee of Johns Hopkins University chairman of Governors Task Force for Funding of Public Education and member of board of directors of Institute against Violence and Prejudice 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP27.HTM#AS7274">Graham: </A><DD>Ronald Graham being director of information sciences at AT&T Bell Laboratories 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP27.HTM#AS727151">Graham's research: </A><DD>Graham's research in combinatorics, graph theory, algorithms, number theory and combinatorial geometry 
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP27.HTM#AS727149">Graph theory: </A><DD>Graham's research in combinatorics, graph theory, algorithms, number theory and combinatorial geometry 
