<HEAD>

<TITLE>Machiavelli's "The Prince"</TITLE>

</HEAD>
<BODY>
<A NAME = "AY"></A>
<A NAME = "AZ"></A>
<A HREF = "HOME.HTM#ANC_HP_TOP"><img src="ANCRBAR.GIF" align=middle></A> <strong>Return to Anchor Page</strong>
&#160;&#160;

<A HREF = "SPP90.HTM#BA"><img src="PREVSEG.GIF" align=middle></A> <strong>Previous</strong>
<hr>
<strong>This is a full-text facsimile of the original document.</STRONG>
<P>


therefore, your illustrious house take up this charge with that 
<P>

courage and hope with which all just enterprises are undertaken, so 
<P>

that under its standard our native country may be ennobled, and 
<P>

under its auspices may be verified that saying of Petrarch: 
<P>

<P>

Virtu contro al Furore 
<P>

Prendera l'arme, e fia il combatter corto: 
<P>

Che l'antico valore 
<P>

Negli italici cuor non e ancor morto.* 
<P>

<P>

* Virtue against fury shall advance the fight, 
<P>

And it i' th'<A NAME = "AO27409"></A><A NAME = "AS274010"></A><A NAME = "AB274011"></A> combat soon shall put to flight; 
<P>

For the old Roman, valour is not dead, 
<P>

Nor in th' Italians' breasts extinguished. 
<P>



THE END 



<P>
&#160;&#160;
<p>
&#160;&#160;

&#160;&#160;

