<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO30169"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendation being consistent with FBI proposal for technical support center to serve as central national law enforcement resource to address problems related to encryption and technological problems with impact on access to electronic communications and stored information 4 <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO301181"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Center to address individuals' use of unescrowed encryption in commission of criminal acts <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO301225"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Open court to deal with problem to be necessary whether escrowed encryption deployed <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO301266"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Second problem of concern to law enforcement authorities obtaining digital stream carrying targeted communications <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO301337"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Law enforcement authorities to need access to technical skill to extract useful information out of digital streams involved <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO301389"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Center to be useful to state and local law enforcement authorities who lack level of access to National Security Agency expertise accorded FBI <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO3031"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>National security authorities recognize <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO30318"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Future capabilities to undertake traditional signals intelligence to be severely challenged by spread of encryption and introduction of new communications media <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO303116"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Losses in traditional signals intelligence capability likely result in diminished effectiveness of U. S. intelligence community <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO303178"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Efforts to develop alternatives to traditional signals intelligence collection techniques to be given high priority in allocation of financial and personnel resources before products covered by Recommendation 4.1 become used <P>
<A NAME = "AK307"></A><H3><B>THE POLICY RELATIONSHIP BETWEEN</B></H2><P><A NAME = "AK310"></A><H3><B>INFORMATION SECURITY AND CRYPTOGRAPHY</B></H2><P><A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO3125"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee asked to address national cryptography policy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO31273"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Changes in national cryptography policy to have little operational impact on U. S. information security <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO31411"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to develop mechanism to promote information security in private sector <P>
<A NAME = "AE3350"></A><A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO3163"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee makes Recommendation 6 based on observation <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO31661"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>No government agency having responsibility to promote information security in private sector <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO31697"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Information security interests of private sector having no formal place at policy-making table <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO316139"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>National Security Agency represents classified government community <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO316164"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Charter of National Institute of Standards and Technology directs to focus on unclassified needs of government <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO316241"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Information Infrastructure Task Force and Office of Management and Budget having broad influence but few operational responsibilities <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO316291"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Business and individual stakeholders not to have adequate representation in development of information security standards and export regimes <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO3189"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Nation requires mechanism to provide accountability and focus for efforts to promote information security in private sector <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO3203"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Importance of close cooperation with private sector not to be overemphasized <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO32032"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government played important role in promoting information security in past <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO32062"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Information security needs in private sector in information age to be larger <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO320116"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Close consultations between government and private sector needed before policy decisions made that affect how needs to be addressed <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO320216"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee believes that policy-making process requires better ways for representing broadly government and nongovernment interests in cryptography policy <P>
<A NAME = "AE3480"></A><A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO3227"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Policy-making process include better representation of nongovernment interests <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO32229"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Private sector advisors or representatives used when policy cuts across functional and organizational boundaries and interests <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO32273"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Inside and outside government and information security falls into cross-cutting category <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO322107"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Government to consider appointment of cleared parties from private sector to participate in government policy discussions relevant to export control decisions or decisions that affect information security interests of private sector <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO322206"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Broad outlines of national cryptography policy to be argued on unclassified basis <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO32474"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Public switched telecommunications network <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO324194"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Government to take and role in collecting and disseminating information to promote awareness of information security threat <P>
<A NAME = "AE3550"></A><A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO32658"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Mechanism to be new coordinating office for information security in Executive Office of President <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO326272"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee believes that NSA being not proper agency to assume primary responsibility for mission oriented toward needs of private sector <P>
<A HREF = "SPP10.HTM#AO326379"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Assistance requires new legislative authority <P>
<A NAME = "AK330"></A><H3><B>CONCLUSION</B></H2><P><A NAME = "AE3590"></A><A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO3323"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee believes that recommendations to lead to enhanced confidentiality and protection of information for individuals and companies reducing economic and financial crimes and economic espionage from domestic and foreign sources <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO33280"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Recommendations to extent contribute to prevention of crime and enhance national security <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO332144"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Government charged with carrying out certain specific law enforcement and intelligence activities <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO332239"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee concluded that interests of government and nation to best to be served by policy that fosters judicious transition toward broad use of cryptography <P>
<A NAME = "AK336"></A><H3><B>THE TEXT OF THE RECOMMENDATIONS</B></H2><P><A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO33810"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>No law to bar manufacture, sale or use of form of encryption within United States <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO34010"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>National cryptography policy to be developed by executive and legislative branches on basis of open public discussion and governed by rule of law <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO34210"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>National cryptography policy affecting development and use of commercial cryptography to be more aligned with market forces <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO3463"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>4.1, Products providing confidentiality at level that meets general commercial requirements to be exportable <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO34644"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Products with encryption capabilities that incorporate 56-bit DES provide level of confidentiality and exportable <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO3483"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>4.2, Products providing stronger confidentiality to be exportable on expedited basis to list of approved companies if proposed product user willing to provide access to decrypted information upon legally authorized request <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO3508"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to streamline and increase transparency of export licensing process for cryptography <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO35212"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to take steps to assist law enforcement and national security to adjust to new technical realities of information age <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO3548"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government actively encourage use of cryptography in nonconfidentiality applications <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO3568"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to promote security of telecommunications networks more actively <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO35644"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to promote link encryption of cellular communications and improvement of security at telephone switches <P>
<A HREF = "SPP11.HTM#AO35824"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to explore escrowed encryption for own uses <P>
<A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO3603"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>5.4, Congress to consider legislation to impose criminal penalties on use of encrypted communications in interstate commerce with intent to commit federal crime <P>
<A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO3623"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>5.5, High priority to be given to research, development and deployment of additional technical capabilities for law enforcement and national security to cope with new technological challenges <P>
<A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO36412"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government to develop mechanism to promote information security in private sector <P>
<A NAME = "AK368"></A><H3><B>NOTES</B></H2><P><A NAME = "AE3800"></A><A NAME = "AE3800"></A><A NAME = "AE3800"></A><A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO3703"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>1 Signals intelligence in general involves collection for intelligence purposes of communications information and information on electronic emissions <P>
<A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO37065"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Signals intelligence used to refer only to aspects of SIGINT referring to communications intelligence <P>
<A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO37165"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Automatic qualification refers to same procedure under which software products using RC2 or RC4 algorithms for confidentiality with 40-bit key sizes qualify for CCL <P>
<A NAME = "AE3830"></A><A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO3725"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>3 Link encryption refers to practice of encrypting information to be communicated <P>
<A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO372128"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cellular call to be encrypted between mobile handset and ground station <P>
<A NAME = "AE3850"></A><A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AO3735"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>4 FBI proposes that TSC to provide law enforcement with capabilities in signals analysis <P>
<A NAME = "AK389"></A><H3><B><I>Cryptography's Role in Securing</I></B></H1><P><A NAME = "AK392"></A><H3><B><I>the Information Society</I></B></H1><P><A NAME = "AK395"></A><H3><B>Preface</B></H1><P><A NAME = "AK399"></A><H3><B>INTRODUCTION</B></H2><P><A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO4019"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptography belonged to governments concerned about protecting own secrets and about asserting prerogatives for access to information relevant to national security and public safety <P>
<A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO40194"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptography policy reflected U. S. government's needs for effective cryptographic protection of classified and other sensitive communications <P>
<A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO401185"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>National security concerns motivated actions as development of cryptographic technologies, development of countermeasures to reverse effects of encryption and control of cryptographic technologies for export <P>
<A NAME = "AE3930"></A><A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO40346"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Industries having come to rely on encryption as enabler of secure electronic funds transfers <P>
<A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO40390"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Other industries developed interest in encryption for protection of proprietary and other sensitive information <P>
<A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO403130"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Broadening use of computers and computer networks generalized demand for technologies to secure communications down to level of individual citizens and assure privacy and security of electronic records and transmissions <P>
<A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO403213"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Increased use of wireless communications highlighted greater vulnerability of communications to unauthorized intercept <P>
<A NAME = "AE3970"></A><A NAME = "AE3970"></A><A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO4057"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Efforts increased to develop encryption systems for private sector use and integrate encryption with other information technology products <P>
<A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO40555"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Interest having grown in commercial market for cryptographic technologies and systems incorporating technologies and nation witnessed heightened debate over individual need and access to technologies to protect individual privacy <P>
<A NAME = "AE3990"></A><A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO4073"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Another consequence of expectation of use of encryption being emergence of law enforcement concerns that parallel national security concerns <P>
<A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO40769"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Law enforcement officials fear that wide dissemination of effective cryptographic technologies to impede efforts to collect information necessary for pursuing criminal investigations <P>
<A HREF = "SPP13.HTM#AO407132"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Civil libertarians fear that controls on cryptographic technologies to give government authorities <P>
<A NAME = "AK411"></A><H3><B>CHARGE OF THE COMMITTEE TO STUDY</B></H2><P><A NAME = "AK414"></A><H3><B>NATIONAL CRYPTOGRAPHY POLICY</B></H2><P><A NAME = "AE4040"></A><A NAME = "AE4040"></A><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO41623"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>National Research Council's Computer Science and Telecommunications Board formed Committee to Study National Cryptography Policy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO41818"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Technology trends with national cryptography policy to keep pace <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO42243"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>U. S. government that describes national cryptography policy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO42424"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Interests affected by national cryptography policy being multiple, varied and related <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO42622"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Debate over cryptography policy hampered by incomplete analysis and discussion of policy options <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO42662"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Proponents of current policy and alternative policies forced into debating positions <P>
<A NAME = "AE4100"></A><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO428149"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Well-defined enemies and U. S. technological, economic and geopolitical dominance to one characterized by rapidly evolving technology, fuzzy lines <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO43013"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>National cryptography policy involves large number of important issues <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO43039"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Important to national cryptography policy as well issues related to deployment of large-scale infrastructure for cryptography and legislation and regulations to support use of cryptography for authentication and data integrity purposes <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO4323"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee focused efforts on issues related to cryptography for confidentiality <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO43243"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee assembled to address at center of public policy debate relates to use of cryptography in confidentiality applications <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO43411"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee reviewed and synthesized relevant material from reports, took written and oral testimony from government, industry and private individuals <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO434129"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Study built upon three prior efforts to examine national cryptography policy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO434236"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>3 A number of other examinations of cryptography or information security policy being important to committee's work <P>
<A NAME = "AK438"></A><H3><B>WHAT THIS REPORT IS NOT</B></H2><P><A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO4403"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Subject of national cryptography policy being complex <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO4425"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report being not comprehensive study of grand trade-offs to be made in other dimensions of national policy to compensate for changes in cryptography policy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO44285"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Relaxing exclusionary rules that govern court admissibility of evidence or installing video cameras in every police helmet as part of package that eliminates restrictions on cryptography <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO442225"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report provide information to help to assess impact of approaches to cryptography policy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP14.HTM#AO442269"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Impact to be weighed against impact of policies related to other areas being outside scope of study and expertise of committee assembled <P>
<A NAME = "AE4240"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO4445"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report being not study on future of National Security Agency in post-Cold War era <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO444103"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report touch on technological trends that affect ability to undertake missions to which cryptography being relevant <P>
<A NAME = "AE4260"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO44611"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report address certain conditions of political, social and technological environment to affect answers <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO44669"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Potential impact on policy of world that offers users possibilities of secure communications <P>
<A NAME = "AE4280"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO4485"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report being not study of computer and communications security <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO44857"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Cryptography being not useful unless part of secure system and responsible for security to be concerned about everything from trustworthiness of individuals writing computer programs to be used to physical security of terminals used to access system <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO448162"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report that addressed system dimensions of computer security being National Research Council report Computers at Risk <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO448210"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Current study draws on report and others to extent relevant for analysis, findings and conclusions about cryptography policy <P>
<A NAME = "AE4320"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO4505"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report being not study of patent disputes having arisen with respect to national cryptography policy in past several years <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO45081"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Holders expect cryptography to assume substantial commercial importance in next several years <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO450115"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Disputes in principle resolvable by U. S. Congress <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO450175"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Key patents to expire in case in relatively near future <P>
<A NAME = "AE4360"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO4525"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Report being not study of national policy associated with Clipper chip <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO45240"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Clipper chip received lion's share of press and notoriety in past few years <P>
<A NAME = "AK456"></A><H3><B>ON SECRECY AND REPORT TIME LINE</B></H2><P><A NAME = "AE4390"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO45811"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Science and technologies associated with cryptography being purview of national governments and heads of state <P>
<A NAME = "AE4400"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO460187"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Public review and discussion of classified information which supports decisions being not feasible <P>
<A NAME = "AE4410"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO4621"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Secrecy being two-edged sword for democratic nation on one hand <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO46232"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Secrecy having legitimate basis in situations in which fundamental national interests at stake <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO46291"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>History of intelligence reveals instances in which revelation of secret having led to compromise of information source or loss of key battle <P>
<A NAME = "AE4440"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO4649"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Secrecy used to stifle public debate and conceal poorly conceived and ill-informed national policies and mistrust being common among responsible critics of government policy <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO464201"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Government hiding poorly conceived policies behind wall of secrecy being not likely to trust government <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO468103"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Relevant agencies complied with Public Law 103-160 and other agencies cooperated with committee <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO468141"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>One important reason being several members of committee having extensive experience with relevant agencies and members heard nothing in briefings held for committee being inconsistent with experience <P>
<A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO468228"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Second reason being agencies having every motivation and self-interest to make best possible case for respective positions on issues before committee <P>
<A NAME = "AE4490"></A><A HREF = "SPP15.HTM#AO470223"><img src="LILABS.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Committee briefed on certain intelligence activities of nations <P>

