<P>
<A NAME = "AE13500"></A><A NAME = "AE13500"></A><A NAME = "AE13500"></A><A NAME = "AE13500"></A><A HREF = "SPP92.HTM#AO274016"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Term alimony means periodic payments of funds for support and maintenance of spouse of individual and includes separate maintenance, alimony pendente lite, maintenance and spousal support and includes attorney's fees, interest and court costs <P>
<A HREF = "SPP92.HTM#AO2740171"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Same made recoverable as such pursuant to decree, order or judgment issued in accordance with applicable State law by court of competent jurisdiction <P>
<A NAME = "AE13520"></A><A NAME = "AE13520"></A><A HREF = "SPP92.HTM#AO274312"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Payment or transfer of property or value by individual to spouse or former spouse of individual in compliance with community property settlement, equitable distribution of property or other division of property between spouses or former spouses <P>
<A HREF = "SPP92.HTM#AO274415"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Term private person means person <P>
<A HREF = "SPP92.HTM#AO274436"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Sovereign or other special immunity or privilege which causes person not to be subject to legal process <P>
<A NAME = "AE13550"></A><A HREF = "SPP92.HTM#AO274812"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Court or administrative agency of competent jurisdiction in foreign country with United States entered into agreement which requires United States to honor process <P>
