<A NAME = "AK2324"></A><h3>SEC. 324. USE OF FORMS IN INTERSTATE ENFORCEMENT.</h3><P><A HREF = "SPP78.HTM#AO23308"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Not later than October 1, 1996 promulgate forms to be used by States in interstate cases <P>
<A NAME = "AE11530"></A><A NAME = "AE11530"></A><A NAME = "AE11530"></A><A NAME = "AE11530"></A><A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO233823"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Using forms promulgated pursuant to section for income withholding, imposition of liens and issuance of administrative subpoenas in interstate child support cases <P>
<A NAME = "AK2340"></A><h3>SEC. 325. STATE LAWS PROVIDING EXPEDITED PROCEDURES.</h3><P><A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO234337"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Expedited administrative and judicial procedures for establishing paternity and establishing, modifying and enforcing support obligations <P>
<A NAME = "AE11560"></A><A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO234619"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Procedures which give State agency authority to take following actions relating to establishment of paternity or establishment, modification or enforcement of support orders <P>
<A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO234682"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Necessity of obtaining order from other judicial or administrative tribunal and recognize and enforce authority of State agencies of other States to take following actions <P>
<A NAME = "AE11580"></A><A NAME = "AE11580"></A><A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO234716"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>To order genetic testing for purpose of paternity establishment as provided in section <P>
<A NAME = "AE11590"></A><A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO234820"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>To subpoena financial or other information needed to establish, modify or enforce support order and impose penalties for failure to respond to such subpoena <P>
<A NAME = "AE11600"></A><A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO235026"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>To obtain access, subject to safeguards on privacy and information security and subject to nonliability of entities that afford such access under subparagraph, information contained in following records <P>
<A NAME = "AE11610"></A><A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO236010"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Certain records held by private entities with respect to individuals who owe or owed support <P>
<A NAME = "AE11620"></A><A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO236173"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Pursuant to administrative subpoena authorized by subparagraph <P>
<A HREF = "SPP79.HTM#AO236211"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Information on such individuals held by financial institutions <P>
<A NAME = "AE11640"></A><A NAME = "AE11640"></A><A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO236360"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>A or section 1912 or requirement to pay through State disbursement unit established pursuant to section 454B, providing notice to obligor and obligee, direct obligor or other payor to change payee to appropriate government entity <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO236910"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Attaching and seizing assets of obligor held in financial institutions <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO237419"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Expedited procedures required under subsection to include following rules and authority enforce support orders <P>
<A NAME = "AE11670"></A><A NAME = "AE11670"></A><A NAME = "AE11670"></A><A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO237610"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Each party to paternity or child support proceeding required to file with tribunal and State case registry upon entry of order and update as appropriate <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO2376123"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Telephone number, driver's license number and name, address and telephone number of employer <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO237738"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Diligent effort made to ascertain location of such party <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO237768"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Tribunal to deem State due process requirements for notice and service of process to be met with respect to party <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO2377114"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Delivery of written notice to residential or employer address filed with tribunal pursuant to clause <P>
<A NAME = "AE11720"></A><A NAME = "AE11720"></A><A NAME = "AE11720"></A><A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO237912"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>State agency and administrative or judicial tribunal with authority to hear child support and paternity cases exerts statewide jurisdiction over parties <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO238014"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>In State in which orders issued by courts or administrative tribunals <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO238039"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Case to be transferred between local jurisdictions in State without need for additional filing by petitioner or service of process upon respondent to retain jurisdiction over parties <P>
<A NAME = "AE11750"></A><A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO2381175"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Such procedure to be consistent with requirements of section of such Act or requirements of section of such Act if reference in such section to domestic relations order and reference in such section to medical child support order being reference to support order referred in paragraphs and relating to same matters <P>
<A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO238316"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>Automated system required by section to be used to implement expedited administrative procedures required by section <P>
<A NAME = "AK2385"></A><h3><center>Subtitle D---Paternity
Establishment</center></h4><P><A NAME = "AK2388"></A><h3>SEC. 331. STATE LAWS CONCERNING PATERNITY
ESTABLISHMENT.</h3><P><A HREF = "SPP80.HTM#AO23907"><img src="ABSTRACT.GIF" ALIGN=MIDDLE></A>STATE LAWS REQUIRED <P>
