 administration of the State law, finds that there is a failure to comply substantially with the requirements of paragraph (1), 
the Secretary<A NAME = "AO224294"></A><A NAME = "AS224295"></A><A NAME = "AB224296"></A> of Labor shall notify such State agency that further payments will not be made to the State until the Secretary of 
Labor is satisfied that there is no longer any such failure. Until the Secretary of Labor is so satisfied, the Secretary<A NAME = "AO2242182"></A> shall make 
no future certification to the Secretary of the Treasury with respect to the State.</ul>
