<p><h3>SEC. 369. STATE LAW AUTHORIZING SUSPENSION OF LICENSES.</h3>
<p><ul>  Section 466(a) (42 U.S.C. 666(a)), as amended by sections 315, 317, 323, and 365 of this Act, is amended by inserting after 
paragraph (15) the following:</ul>
<p><ul><ul>   (16) AUTHORITY<A NAME = "AO28488"></A><A NAME = "AS28489"></A> TO WITHHOLD OR SUSPEND<A NAME = "AB284818"></A> LICENSES-- Procedures<A NAME = "AO284824"></A><A NAME = "AS284825"></A><A NAME = "AS284826"></A><A NAME = "AS284827"></A><A NAME = "AS284828"></A><A NAME = "AS284829"></A> under which the State has (and uses in appropriate cases) 
