<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP82.HTM#AS243334">Registry of birth records: </A><DD>Procedures under which voluntary acknowledgments and adjudications of paternity by judicial or administrative processes filed with State registry of birth records for comparison with information in State case registry
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS38229">Reimbursement categories: </A><DD>Placing home into 1 of 2 or more reimbursement categories annually based on percentage of children in home of which households having incomes that meet income eligibility guidelines under section 9
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS382283">Reimbursement category: </A><DD>Each such reimbursement category carrying set of reimbursement factors such as factors prescribed under clause or subclause or factors established within range of factors prescribed under clause and subclause
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP127.HTM#AS379919">Reimbursement factors: </A><DD>Institution that participates in program under section as family or group day care home sponsoring organization to be provided reimbursement factors in accordance with subparagraph for cost of obtaining and preparing food and prescribed labor costs involved in providing meals under section
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS380532">Reimbursement factors: </A><DD>Tier I family or group day care home to be provided reimbursement factors under clause without requirement for documentation of costs described in clause
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS380718">Reimbursement factors: </A><DD>Reimbursement factors under subparagraph to be adjusted on July 1, 1997 and each July 1 to reflect changes in Consumer Price Index for food at home for 12-month period For which data being available
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS3807111">Reimbursement factors: </A><DD>Reimbursement factors under subparagraph to be rounded to nearest lower cent increment and based on unrounded adjustment in effect on June 30 of preceding school year
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS381195">Reimbursement factors: </A><DD>Reimbursement factors under item to be rounded down to nearest lower cent increment and based on unrounded adjustment for preceding 12-month period
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS381214">Reimbursement factors: </A><DD>Family or group day care home to be provided reimbursement factors under subclause without requirement for documentation of costs described in clause
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS3814100">Reimbursement factors: </A><DD>Family or group day care home to be provided reimbursement factors set by Secretary in accordance with clause
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS381571">Reimbursement factors: </A><DD>Family or group day care home to be provided reimbursement factors in accordance with subclause
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP39.HTM#AS116835">Religion: </A><DD>Not discriminate against individual in regard to rendering assistance funded under program described in subsection on basis of religion
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP38.HTM#AS115916">Religious organization: </A><DD>Religious organization with contract described in subsection or accepts
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP38.HTM#AS116018">Religious organization: </A><DD>Federal Government or State to require religious organization
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP39.HTM#AS117030">Religious organization: </A><DD>Religious organization contracting to provide assistance funded under program described in subsection to be subject to same regulations as other contractors to account in accord with accepted auditing principles for use of such funds provided under such programs
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP39.HTM#AS116717">Religious organization's exemption: </A><DD>Religious organization's exemption provided under section 702 of Civil Rights Act of 1964 regarding employment practices
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP38.HTM#AS115615">Religious organizations: </A><DD>Purpose of section to allow States to contract with religious organizations or allow religious organizations to accept
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP38.HTM#AS115616">Religious organizations: </A><DD>Purpose of section to allow States to contract with religious organizations or allow religious organizations to accept
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP39.HTM#AS117411">Religious organizations: </A><DD>Nothing in section to be construed to preempt provision of State constitution or State statute that prohibits or restricts expenditure of State funds by religious organizations
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP93.HTM#AS277631">Residential address: </A><DD>Address for member of Armed Forces shown in locator service to be residential address of member
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP51.HTM#AS1542168">Resources of household: </A><DD>Income and resources of individual to be considered to be income and resources of household
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP152.HTM#AS450422">Retail food store: </A><DD>Term point-of-sale service means product or service related to electronic authorization and processing of payments for merchandise at retail food store including credit or debit card services
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP153.HTM#AS454465">Retail food store: </A><DD>No retail food store or wholesale food concern of type determined by Secretary based on factors that include size
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP153.HTM#AS455961">Retail food store: </A><DD>Retail food store or wholesale food concern denied approval to accept and redeem coupons because store or concern
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP156.HTM#AS464361">Retail food store: </A><DD>Regulations issued pursuant to Act to provide criteria for finding of violation and suspension or disqualification of retail food store or wholesale food concern on basis of evidence to include facts established through on-site investigations, inconsistent redemption data or evidence obtained through transaction report under electronic benefit transfer system
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP157.HTM#AS465719">Retail food store: </A><DD>Secretary to issue regulations providing criteria for disqualification under Act of approved retail food store or wholesale food concern disqualified from accepting benefits under special supplemental nutrition program for women, infants and children established under section 17 of Child Nutrition Act of 1966
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP158.HTM#AS469137">Retail food store: </A><DD>Permanent disqualification of retail food store or wholesale food concern under paragraph or section to be effective from date of receipt of notice of disqualification
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP153.HTM#AS455529">Retail food stores: </A><DD>Regulations to require retail food stores and wholesale food concerns to provide written authorization for Secretary to verify relevant tax filings with appropriate agencies and obtain corroborating documentation from other sources
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP90.HTM#AS267216">Right to Financial Privacy Act of 1978: </A><DD>Term financial record having meaning given such term in section 1101 of Right to Financial Privacy Act of 1978
<P><A NAME = "AX6099"></A>&#160;
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP153.HTM#AS455413">Sales tax filing documents: </A><DD>First sentence, inserting to include relevant income and sales tax filing documents, submit information
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP20.HTM#AS610207">School diploma: </A><DD>Secondary school diploma or recognized equivalent unless such adult determined in judgment of medical, psychiatric or other appropriate professionals to lack requisite capacity to complete course of study to lead to secondary school diploma or recognized equivalent
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP20.HTM#AS610208">School diploma: </A><DD>Secondary school diploma or recognized equivalent unless such adult determined in judgment of medical, psychiatric or other appropriate professionals to lack requisite capacity to complete course of study to lead to secondary school diploma or recognized equivalent
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP126.HTM#AS375919">School food authority: </A><DD>School food authority participating as service institution to permit child attending site on school premises operated directly by authority to refuse one or more items of meal
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP127.HTM#AS378210">School lunch program: </A><DD>Each State agency that receives food assistance payments under section for school year to consult with representatives of schools in State that participate in school lunch program with respect to needs of such schools relating to manner of selection and distribution of commodity assistance for such program
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP137.HTM#AS408117">School lunch program: </A><DD>Secretary of Agriculture to develop proposed changes to regulations under school lunch program under National School Lunch Act
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS380311">School meals: </A><DD>Family or group day care home located in area served by school enrolling elementary students in which at least 50 percent of total number of children enrolled being certified eligible to receive free or reduced price school meals under Act or Child Nutrition Act of 1966
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP12.HTM#AS37612">School performance: </A><DD>Absence of father in life of child having negative effect on school performance and peer adjustment
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP126.HTM#AS375918">School premises: </A><DD>School food authority participating as service institution to permit child attending site on school premises operated directly by authority to refuse one or more items of meal
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP127.HTM#AS378211">School year: </A><DD>Each State agency that receives food assistance payments under section for school year to consult with representatives of schools in State that participate in school lunch program with respect to needs of such schools relating to manner of selection and distribution of commodity assistance for such program
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP128.HTM#AS3807110">School year: </A><DD>Reimbursement factors under subparagraph to be rounded to nearest lower cent increment and based on unrounded adjustment in effect on June 30 of preceding school year
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP48.HTM#AS14508">School-To-Work Opportunities Act of 1994: </A><DD>Subparagraph of section of School-To-Work Opportunities Act of 1994 amended to read as follows
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP130.HTM#AS387514">Secretary of Agriculture data: </A><DD>Each State agency participating in child and adult care food program under section 17 of National School Lunch Act to submit to Secretary of Agriculture data
<P><DT><A HREF = "SPP39.HTM#AS117930">Secretary of Commerce: </A><DD>Secretary of Commerce to expand Bureau's census question
